article.headline: Louisiana Tech 71, Hawaii 70
article.story: RUSTON, La. (AP) -- Paul Millsap sank a free throw with 0.4 seconds remaining to give Louisiana Tech a 71-70 victory over Hawaii Thursday night. Millsap finished with a game-high 29 points and 13 rebounds to help the Bulldogs (12-9, 7-5 Western Athletic) to their fifth win in the past six games. Wayne Powell added 18 points for Tech and Donell Allick had 13. Powell also had 10 rebounds. Hawaii (13-6, 5-6) was led by Jake Sottos' 23 points. Matt Gibson had 15 and Jeff Blackett added 10. Tech had a 41-31 halftime lead before Sottos' outside shooting -- he hit on five 3-pointers -- helped bring the Rainbow Warriors back in the final half. Hawaii had a 70-65 lead with 2:08 remaining before the Bulldogs went on a 6-0 run to close out the game.
